<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="173">M. alopecuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in south-western U.S.A., Mexico and disjunct in Argentina and Bolivia (
<bibRefCitation author="Davidse, G" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the Torrey Botanical Club" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" refId="B4" refString="Davidse, G, Pohl, RW, 1994. 262. Poaceae. In: Davidse G, Sousa SM, Chater AO (Eds) Flora Mesoamericana, Volumen 6, Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Instituto de Biologia, Mexico, D.F., 184-402." title="262. Poaceae. In: Davidse G, Sousa SM, Chater AO (Eds) Flora Mesoamericana, Volumen 6, Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Instituto de Biologia, Mexico, D. F., 184 - 402." year="1994">Davidse and Pohl 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Renvoize, SA" journalOrPublisher="Phytologia" pageId="59" pageNumber="182" refId="B52" refString="Renvoize, SA, 1998. Gramineas de Bolivia. The Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, 1-644." title="Gramineas de Bolivia. The Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, 1 - 644." year="1998">Renvoize 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reeder, CG" journalOrPublisher="Phytologia" pageId="59" pageNumber="182" refId="B50" refString="Reeder, CG, 2003. 17.34 Lycurus Kunth. In: Barkworth ME, Capels KM, Long S, Piep MB (Eds) Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 2 Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol 25. Oxford University Press, New York, 200-203." title="17.34 Lycurus Kunth. In: Barkworth ME, Capels KM, Long S, Piep MB (Eds) Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 2 Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol 25. Oxford University Press, New York, 200 - 203." year="2003">Reeder 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="Caldasia" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" refId="B29" refString="Peterson, PM, Giraldo-Canas, D, 2012. Muhlenbergia Schreb. In: Zuloaga FO, Rugolo ZE, Anton AMR (Eds) Flora Argentina, Flora Vascular de la Republica Argentina, Vol. 3, Tomo 1, Monocotyledoneae, Poaceae: Aristidoideae a Pharoideae. IBODA-IMBIV, CONICET, Buenos Aires, Argentina, 140-154." title="Muhlenbergia Schreb. In: Zuloaga FO, Rugolo ZE, Anton AMR (Eds) Flora Argentina, Flora Vascular de la Republica Argentina, Vol. 3, Tomo 1, Monocotyledoneae, Poaceae: Aristidoideae a Pharoideae. IBODA-IMBIV, CONICET, Buenos Aires, Argentina, 140 - 154." year="2012">
Peterson and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Giraldo-Cañas">Giraldo-Canas</normalizedToken>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. M. Peterson &amp; Columbus" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Griseb." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia alopecuroides" order="Poales" pageId="50" pageNumber="173" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alopecuroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="173">Muhlenbergia alopecuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. phalaroides" order="Poales" pageId="50" pageNumber="173" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="phalaroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="173">M. phalaroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having leaf blades with terminal seta (3-)4-7(-12) mm long and ligules(2-)3-12 mm long whereas 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. phleoides" order="Poales" pageId="50" pageNumber="173" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="phleoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="173">M. phleoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having auriculate ligules 1-2 mm long (
<bibRefCitation author="Reeder, CG" journalOrPublisher="Phytologia" pageId="59" pageNumber="182" pagination="283 - 291" refId="B49" refString="Reeder, CG, 1985. The genus Lycurus (Gramineae) in North America. Phytologia 57: 283 - 291" title="The genus Lycurus (Gramineae) in North America." volume="57" year="1985">Reeder 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reeder, CG" journalOrPublisher="Phytologia" pageId="59" pageNumber="182" refId="B50" refString="Reeder, CG, 2003. 17.34 Lycurus Kunth. In: Barkworth ME, Capels KM, Long S, Piep MB (Eds) Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 2 Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol 25. Oxford University Press, New York, 200-203." title="17.34 Lycurus Kunth. In: Barkworth ME, Capels KM, Long S, Piep MB (Eds) Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 2 Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol 25. Oxford University Press, New York, 200 - 203." year="2003">2003</bibRefCitation>
). These morphological differences are perhaps better recognised at the subspecific level but there have been no population studies comparing these three species, other than 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="Madrono" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="334 - 346" refId="B31" refString="Peterson, PM, Morrone, O, 1997. Allelic variation in the amphitropical disjunct Lycurus setosus (Poaceae: Muhlenbergiinae). Madrono 44: 334 - 346" title="Allelic variation in the amphitropical disjunct Lycurus setosus (Poaceae: Muhlenbergiinae)." volume="44" year="1997">Peterson and Morrone (1997)</bibRefCitation>
who investigated populations of only the amphitropical, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. alocpecuroides" order="Poales" pageId="50" pageNumber="173" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="alocpecuroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="173">M. alocpecuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Reeder" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="Nutt." class="Anthozoa" family="Gramineae" genus="Lycurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lycurus setosus" order="Poales" pageId="50" pageNumber="173" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="setosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="173">Lycurus setosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="50" pageNumber="173">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia phalaroides" order="Poales" pageId="50" pageNumber="173" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phalaroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="173">Muhlenbergia phalaroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lies within 
<taxonomicName authority="subg. Pseudosporobolus" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="subg." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M." order="Poales" pageId="50" pageNumber="173" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus" subGenus="Pseudosporobolus">M. subg. Pseudosporobolus</taxonomicName>
, aligning with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. alopecuroides" order="Poales" pageId="50" pageNumber="173" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="alopecuroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="173">M. alopecuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. phleoides" order="Poales" pageId="50" pageNumber="173" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="phleoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="173">M. phleoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Peterson and Romaschenko, in prep.). Many members of this subgenus have narrow 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="173">panicles</emphasis>
, plumbeous spikelets with unawned, mucronate or short-awned lemmas (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="59" pageNumber="182" pagination="1532 - 1554" refId="B38" refString="Peterson, PM, Romaschenko, K, Johnson, G, 2010b. A phylogeny and classification of the Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae) based on plastid and nuclear DNA sequences. American Journal of Botany 97 (9): 1532 - 1554, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" title="A phylogeny and classification of the Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae) based on plastid and nuclear DNA sequences." url="https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" volume="97" year="2010 b">Peterson et al. 2010b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
